In emacs 27 there are two new commands included 'undo-only and 'undo-redo. They are equivalent to undo and redo in other editors. So a config like:

(global-set-key [remap undo] 'undo-only)
(global-set-key (kbd "C-M-_") 'undo-redo)

should be enough without any external package.

-- Ergus 2020-06-09 00:32 UTC


